INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (245701, 'GOD couldn''t love you more than He already does', 42910, 0), (245702, 'Hatred, like a bush fire, ultimately consumes those who propagate it, leaving nothing but scorched, barren earth behind in their hearts. Love, the greatest of reckless endeavours, inspires men to greatness in the face of seemingly insurmountable odds... Maybe this book is just that, a reckless endeavour of the heart.', 22180, 0), (245703, 'Love me or hate me, both are in my favour. If you love me, I''ll always be in your heart... If you hate me, I''ll always be in your mind.', 13, 0), (245704, 'You cannot change someone using fear, degradation, humiliation, or by comparing them to others. It can only be done through love, with love, for love.', 2678, 0), (245705, 'I wish I could hold you," she continued bitterly, "till we were both dead!', 55, 0), (245706, 'People say hate is like a poison — but they''re wrong. It''s like a drug. You never forget your first hit, how it seduces you with its strength and power, and takes you completely by storm. It colors your world in light and meaning, until you wonder how you ever managed to get by without it. And then, eventually, you get to a point where you can''t. It takes over your life, until hating becomes your reason for living.', 2534, 0), (245707, 'I love my ex so much I printed out all his pictures. After all, I need him for target practice. And I just love customised toilet paper and doormats. My only regret is that those items don''t bear his autograph.', 6973, 0), (245708, 'Odi et amo. Quare id faciam, fortasse requiris. Nescio. des fieri sentio et excrucior.I hate and I love. You may ask, why I do this. I do not know. But I sense that I do and it pains me.', 8877, 0), (245709, 'But I am also concerned about our moral uprightness and the health of our souls. Therefore I must oppose any attempt to gain our freedom by the methods of malice, hate, and violence that have characterized our oppressors. Hate is just as injurious to the hater as it is to the hated. Like an unchecked cancer, hate corrodes the personality and eats away its vital unity. Many of our inner conflicts are rooted in hate. This is why psychiatrists say, “Love or perish.” Hate is too great a burden to bear.', 5, 0), (245710, 'Unable to understand why you think so, when you chose a different path.', 42911, 0), (245711, 'Don’t hate on someone whose hard work placed them on the road to success, while your envy and ill-intent put you on a path toward failure.', 5323, 0), (245712, 'The walls that a hateful mind builds around it, make it impossible for happiness to find its way in.', 166, 0), (245713, 'It''s quite unfortunate how some people would like you when you are barely making ends meet, but would hate you with a passion if you start to do well.', 166, 0), (245714, 'Some people hate the rain, other appreciate it for the blooming flowers.', 920, 0), (245715, 'You deepen the injury. It is sufficient already.', 96, 0), (245716, 'Silly Felix, hate and love are the flip sides of the same tarnished coin.', 30525, 0), (245717, '...I knew in the end the guilt of one side did not prove the innocence of the other.', 16275, 0), (245718, 'It''s not love that you hate, it''s the loved one who betrayed.', 15139, 0), (245719, 'She dared to cry? On this day of all days? I was the one who would be married at sunset, and I hadn''t let myself cry in five years. There was ice in my lungs and in my heart. I was floating. I was swept away, and out of the cold I spoke to her in a voice as soft as snow, the gentle and obedient voice I had used to consent to every order that Father and Aunt Telomache ever gave me, every order that they would never give Astraia because they actually loved her."You know, that Rhyme is a lie that Aunt Telomache only told you because you weren''t strong enough to bear the truth."I had thought the words so often, they felt like nothing in my mouth, like no more than a breath of air, and as easily as breathing I went on."The truth is, Mother died because of you, and now I have to die for your sake, too. And neither one of us will ever forgive you."Then I shoved her aside and strode out of the room.', 481, 0), (245720, 'My sister compares her body to a junkyard and I find bits of scrap metal beneath her bed from boys who bury promises in her belly. Maybe love ruins you a little bit. Maybe we don’t care. We are so young to hate everything so much. Can recite the periodic table from memory but still can’t quite believe it when they say that they love us, too.', 42715, 0), (245721, 'But I am very poorly today & very stupid & I hate everybody & everything. One lives only to make blunders.', 1024, 0), (245722, 'Life is so transient, finite, and fragile that there is no time to hate anyone.', 2586, 0), (245723, 'We often hate others because we fail to understand them.', 2586, 0), (245724, 'We fear something before we hate it', 42912, 0), (245725, 'I have not met this person, and yet I hate him more than anything, for in him is everything I hate.', 24787, 0), (245726, 'Your mission: Be so busy loving your life that you have no time for hate, regret or fear.', 5238, 0), (245727, 'If you’d rather not go with me, I will completely understand and won’t hate you for more than a day. Maybe two.', 1038, 0), (245728, 'Men have always hated the wolf.""Why?" said the boy indignantly, suddenly looking very unhappy indeed."Maybe because they see something in the wolf that they hate and fear in themselves. Maybe because wolves take their sheep and goats, as if we shouldn''t all share life''s bounty.', 23494, 0), (245729, 'I know she hates me, yet cannot choose but love her: No matter, if but to vex her, I''ll haunt her still; Though I get nothing else, I''ll have my will.', 2906, 0), (245730, 'Love me or hate me, both are in my favor. If you love me, I''ll always be in your heart. If you hate me, I''ll always be in your mind.', 13, 0), (245731, 'You are not doing this for her. You''re doing it for yourself. Your life is not just about the people you love. It''s also about the people you hate.', 24556, 0), (245732, 'Animosity breeds chaos.', 30739, 0), (245733, 'When we continue to hate, we continue to lose. When we amplify mutual respect and love, we have a lot to gain. Quite simply, there is more for us to gain through love than hate.', 2678, 0), (245734, 'I''ve always looked at America like a foster mother doing it only for the check. At any minute, I just knew she''d be ready to give up on me.', 4531, 0), (245735, 'Love is as irrational as hate and just as unpredictable.', 884, 0), (245736, 'wars are fought so that peace can be achieved talk about irony', 42913, 0), (245737, 'Only the unloved hate', 42914, 0), (245738, 'If Fred''s history will seem less unbiased then some would wish, let it never be overlooked that it is no small task to record a history of hate when one is among the hated.', 17166, 0), (245739, 'We are not enemies but we are just hostile to each other because of our different views and opinions.', 5089, 0), (245740, 'Shall not ILearn place and wisdom? Have I not learned this,Only so much to hate my enemy,As though he might again become my friend,And so much good to wish to do my friend,As knowing he may yet become my foe?', 139, 0), (245741, 'A man once told me that there are infinite places love will take you, but revenge is the business of hate, and there is only one place hate will take you---the end. The end of you and the end of everything you once stood for. But I welcomed my end.', 38228, 0), (245742, 'The way he looks at me makes me ache, but it isn’t fair. He hurt me first. He caused this ache from the start. This inside out, churning pain that feels mental and physical now.I fiddle with my hands, peering up at him again, and all I can think is, God, I wish he’d stop staring at me like that.', 23436, 0), (245743, 'Hate is self-inflicted torture. It hungers for revenge, damage, division, and violence, but is never satiated. Hate is a psychological hell to which we condemn ourselves and endeavor to burn others.', 161, 0), (245744, 'Gilbert?"Some days I hate all those who know my name.', 19869, 0), (245745, 'I''m God. I will give you love and never hate you. I''ll give you all the comforts you''ve ever imagined. Because I''m the God.', 34762, 0), (245746, 'He came up flailing and sputtering and began to thrash his way toward the line of willows that marked the submerged creek bank. He could not swim, but how would you drown him? His wrath seemed to buoy him up. Some halt in the way of things seems to work here. See him. You could say that he''s sustained by his fellow men, like you. Has peopled the shore with them calling to him. A race that gives suck to the maimed and the crazed, that wants their wrong blood in its history and will have it. But they want this man''s life. He has heard them in the night seeking him with lanterns and cries of execration. How then is he borne up? Or rather, why will not these waters take him?', 548, 0), (245747, 'Tereza''s death hurt me so much, it was as if I had two heads smashing into each other. One was full of mown love, the other of hate. I wanted the love to grow back. It grew like grass and straw, all mixed up together, and turned into an icy affirmation on my brow. That was my damn stupid plant.', 14581, 0), (245748, 'The weak-minded choose to hate," she said. "It''s the least painful thing to do, isn''t it?', 3787, 0), (245749, 'That child of Hell had nothing human', 42915, 0), (245750, 'I met a woman who told me she wasn''t attracted to Asians. No worries, I said. I''m not attracted to racists.', 16685, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (245751, 'We are rich in hearts, but poor with love.', 3341, 0), (245752, 'Man''s meanness is a fuse in search of a flame.', 252, 0), (245753, 'Pain withheld becomes hate, pain shared becomes love.', 12171, 0), (245754, 'Don''t expect everyone to admire this world is made up of hate and fire.', 25357, 0), (245755, 'His mama put down the bag and headed for the door, her mouth a thin line.	“Wait! What are you doing? Don’t go over there and yell at her.” Paul jumped off the stool and tried to beat her to the door. 	“Oh, honey, I would never do that.” His mama stepped into the hallway. “I’m fixin’ to invite her for dinner.', 31722, 0), (245756, 'Promoting what you don''t like, invites more of it to your doorstep. Beat the right drum. ~T.F. Hodge', 2747, 0), (245757, 'Hate feeds on your heart and pollutes your mind. It makes you lose sight of reality and forces you to focus on animosity instead of love. Hate makes you less of a person, because the borders of hate are so expansive they leave no room for anything else, and then the rest of your world becomes tiny and insignificant in comparison.', 20922, 0), (245758, 'Jealousy is a general human behavior, Until it''s not changed.', 42916, 0), (245759, 'Love is the strongest motivator of all, Reagan. Stronger than fear, stronger than hate, stronger than whatever else is out there. Love is more than enough to survive with; it''s enough to live with.', 15976, 0), (245760, 'We tend to search for happiness and love forgetting that both can be found when we stop searching for sadness and hate.', 5009, 0), (245761, 'She represents something about the corporate world that repel me, some deep coldness masked as relentless cheerfulness.', 10605, 0), (245762, 'There are some we cannot help but take an instant dislike to.', 923, 0), (245763, 'It''s easier to hate than to hurt.', 15125, 0), (245764, 'I could never hate you, even if I wanted to.', 1421, 0), (245765, 'A coward''s gun is emptied when fear pulls the trigger, and hate is the ammunition of choice.', 2747, 0), (245766, 'We need an enemy to give people hope. Someone said that patriotism is the last refuge of cowards: those without moral principles usually wrap a flag around themselves, and the bastards always talk about the purity of the race. National identity is the last bastion of the dispossessed. But the meaning of identity is now based on hatred, on hatred for those who are not the same. Hatred has to be cultivated as a civic passion. The enemy is the friend of the people. You always want someone to hate in order to feel justified in your own misery. Hatred is the primordial passion. It is love that’s abnormal.', 736, 0), (245767, 'What you hate the most, stays with you, while the loved ones walk away.', 1527, 0), (245768, 'There are plenty of good reasons for fighting, but no good reason ever to hate without reservation, to imagine that God Almighty Himself hates with you, too.', 134, 0), (245769, 'Dictators long ago found that it is easier to unite people in common hatred than in common love.', 29049, 0), (245770, 'Hate has no ears.', 14766, 0), (245771, 'You don''t realize it and that is why you hate who you are. You are living as someone else, so you unknowingly destroy that image everyday.', 3527, 0), (245772, '210Suffering engenders passion; and while the prosperous blind themselves, or go to sleep, the hatred of the unfortunate classes kindles its torch at some sullen or ill-constituted mind, which is dreaming in a corner, and sets to work to examine society. The examination of hatred is a terrible thing.”Suffering begets rage, and while the prosperous turn a blind eye, or nod off which is always the same thing as shutting your eyes, the hate of the unprosperous masses has hits torch lit by some malcontent or warped mind dreaming away in a corner, somewhere, and it begins to examine society. Examination by hate is a terrible thing.', 98, 0), (245773, 'I''m supposed to hate you for what you did, I think. But her eyes linger on me in a way that refuses to let me.', 237, 0), (245774, 'God'' is an excuse to justify hate.', 33, 0), (245775, 'A friend is like a rope, you trust it until it snaps.', 5089, 0), (245776, 'And everything I thought I knew - you made me trade it all for you...but, frankly, you''re not worth it.', 26808, 0), (245777, 'Hatred is like fire. It burns the one who harnesses it. It''s also extremely hard to see more helpful truths through its flames.', 1598, 0), (245778, 'The Creator favors the man who LOVES over the man who HATES. If you teach hatred to your children, one day your child will have that hatred reflected back onto them and onto YOU.', 2678, 0), (245779, 'I don''t hate you, because hate is a feeling and I feel absolutely nothing for you.', 5089, 0), (245780, 'I hate often and easily. I hate, for example, people who sit with their legs splayed. People who claim to give 110 percent. People who call themselves "comfortable" when what they mean is decadently rich. You''re so judgmental, my shrink tells me, and I cry all the way home, thinking of it.', 10830, 0), (245781, 'It''s fallacious reasoning for the atheist to hate all religion due to men who manipulate religion to fit their own agendas. They are counterparts, therefore, if Truth is true, partners in crime. To believers, the atheist and the religiously corrupt boil down to the same person, the self-righteous: one denies Truth to fit his own agenda; the other manipulates Truth to fit his own agenda.', 230, 0), (245782, 'Tolerance is certainly an improvement over hate, but it is not the same thing as freedom.', 42917, 0), (245783, 'The love hidden within is always greater than the hate displayed without.', 4397, 0), (245784, 'He''s mad at me.""For what?""For not being like him."Eleanor looked dubious. "Has he been mad at you for the last sixteen years?""Basically.', 54, 0), (245785, 'Distance can make a love fade, while closeness can make hate flare; as distance can make hate fade, while closeness can make love flare.', 3341, 0), (245786, 'The bacteria of resentment bred: distance turned to distrust; distrust turned to bitterness; bitterness to hate, which is, after all, a kind of grievous love', 22202, 0), (245787, 'Without virtue, it is hard to bear the results of good fortune suitably. Those who lack virtue become arrogant and wantonly aggressive when they have these other goods. They think less of everyone else, and do whatever they please. They do this because they are imitating the magnanimous person though they are not really like him.', 29068, 0), (245788, 'Everyone is capable of hate, of wanting to hurt, even kill another person. But when those hatreds manifest themselves out of the mind and into real life, a line is crossed. The line between human and animal.', 14136, 0), (245789, 'Harbour love, not hate - don''t let it contaminate your heart and conceal your beauty.', 42918, 0), (245790, 'How may I hate that which I love with such intensity of passion? How should I abhor that for which my every drop of blood is boiling?', 41120, 0), (245791, 'Some might say; loving is worse than hating, yet leaving is the worst.', 23477, 0), (245792, 'It began with a hello, and ended in hell.', 3341, 0), (245793, 'People will try to break you, hate you, ignore youBut if you accept them with love, nothing will touch you.', 2586, 0), (245794, 'We hated each other so well and loved each other so badly...', 3385, 0), (245795, 'Some kinds of misery make you hate the world, but some kinds make you hate yourself, and--butter and cheese not withstanding--Neve had no question that Spear was the latter.', 287, 0), (245796, 'All hate is the result of people refusing to take responsibility for their own lives.', 884, 0), (245797, 'Hemingway is overrated,Twain is even more lost at sea,And all truths point to the mouth of a woman,Where both her whispers and her screams,Are born.Pour another glass, Beer, wine, whiskey,I don''t care,So long as its wisdom is sharp,And it tells lies instead of promises.', 2877, 0), (245798, 'The world is getting too small for both an Us and a Them. Us and Them have become codependent, intertwined, fixed to one another. We have no separate fates, but are bound together in one. And our fear of one another is the only thing capable of our undoing.', 15477, 0), (245799, 'Hating is easy. It''s loving that''s hard', 25901, 0), (245800, 'She put others before herself and yet you hate her. What did she do to you?', 42919, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (245801, 'Love and hatred are intertwined in life. They agree to disagree and they disagree to agree. When one is absent the other may become present. In what we hate most lay what we love most and in what we love most lay what we hate most', 4606, 0), (245802, 'Bureaucrats and Politicians are different people, work of Bureaucrats makes us hate Politicians.', 589, 0), (245803, 'It’s gotten far easier to allow ourselves to hate than it is to choose to love.', 15477, 0), (245804, 'if you hate someone..wish he love someone.', 21380, 0), (245805, 'Hate. The word is thrown around as uselessly and as often as love is, and is used as a means in which to accuse and inflict damage; the weak-in-argument (weak in general) use it to discredit those with whom they disagree rather than dissect the issues for what they really are. I liken it to the predictable ad hominem attack, which is about as transparent as those who so ridiculously claim to know what’s in the heart of another.', 3711, 0), (245806, 'Our heart is the key to liberating a generation that has been bred to hate.', 3527, 0), (245807, 'I will always hate war, but will be forever proud of mine.', 24649, 0), (245808, 'You can do the right thing that seems wrong to others, or the wrong thing that seems right, and its actually puerile to await recommendation when what you are about to do doesn''t concerns anyone.', 332, 0), (245809, 'I will never forget seeing what hate can destroy… I will never forget seeing what love can heal…', 161, 0), (245810, 'You know all about love, but that is not enough. You must also learn that hate comes from God as well, that it too is in the Lord''s service. And in times like these, with the world fallen to the state it has, hate serves God more than love.', 1048, 0), (245811, 'Hate is a very strong, pure emotion to be wasted on people you don''t care about.', 16654, 0), (245812, 'There is nothing so moving - not even acts of love or hate - as the discovery that one is not alone.', 7179, 0), (245813, 'I let the curtains fall back against the glass, effectively blocking the view of my nemesis standing there beneath the twinkle lights, looking way too hot in his charcoal-colored suit.It would be so much easier to hate him if he didn''t look so good. And I want to hate him; I really do.', 13143, 0), (245814, 'Law & order embrace on hate''s border.', 16400, 0), (245815, 'Love them that hate you, but you can''t love those you hate.', 93, 0), (245816, 'A silence absorbed them both – a lack of sound so potent it blackened the place with something richer than hate.', 14195, 0), (245817, 'If I had a wish, I would turn you to a pair of shoes to keep you under my feet and you get an opportunity to be under the bed too.', 7743, 0), (245818, 'The eternal wave of hate never stops.', 36414, 0), (245819, 'When you look through the window of hate, you are really looking in the Devil''s mirror.', 42920, 0), (245820, 'The only person you can fiercely hate is the person you have loved once fiercely, with your whole heart.', 33, 0), (245821, 'People have been bred to hate for generations -- eons, maybe. Some fundamental urge. Something implicit in the human condition.', 24652, 0), (245822, 'Clouds shed the agony of the sky and rain concludes it by covering us in filth. What do you think about the puddles of mud and traffic jams? I so hate rain.', 7743, 0), (245823, 'You must thrive to flood the nose and mouth of those who hate you and can''t wait to see you fail.', 24659, 0), (245824, 'People always have reason to hate, though they often may not find any reason for love.', 11233, 0), (245825, 'They left like you knew they would. They went away and you fell like a stone. All the way to the bottom of your room. I see you, yes I see you. Sitting in your chair, hating every minute of it. Falling like a stone without even moving. It hurt you to know that you were right about all the shit you wanted to be wrong about. They always leave you. You put yourself in the right place to get left.', 68, 0), (245826, 'This was why I hated beautiful people. They build you up and then they destroy you. And we let ''em.', 8155, 0), (245827, 'We both disliked rude rickshwalas, shepu bhaji in any form, group photographs at weddings, lizards, tea that has gone cold, the habit of taking newspaper to the toilet, kissing a boy who''d just smoked a cigarette et cetra. Another list. The things we loved: strong coffee, Matisse, Rumi, summer rain, bathing together, Tom Hanks, rice pancakes, Cafe Sunrise, black-and-white photographs, the first quiet moments after you wake up in the morning.', 13212, 0), (245828, 'At some point they show their true colorsAfter the break upAfter the trial After the contract is signed and brokenTheir true colors stinkThese daysI find it hard to get along with themI want to push them until the colors come out And sometimes I hate them so much, I push and seeI do the same to the ones I likeThe ones I don’t care about I smile at real nice', 68, 0), (245829, 'Those who cannot have your love, will gladly accept your hatred.', 10831, 0), (245830, 'Another thing that happens in the movies: They all have these dramatic crises where everything looks bleak and you think the couple will never, ever get back together. But then they realize they can''t live without each other, and in the end they live happily ever after.It''s all a lie. When you hate someone you used to love, and you think he''s done something awful-he probably has.You''re not going to love him again.He''s not going to apologize, or come back to you.He probably doesn''t even ever think about you at all, because he''s too busy thinking about someone else.', 447, 0), (245831, 'Hate yearned to destroy and sought to forget, but love could not. Love strove creatively towards days that had yet to come.', 2905, 0), (245832, 'I had a dream that I had no haters…I woke up missing them.', 33086, 0), (245833, 'Hate when hate acquaints the burns,Love when love heals it!', 23388, 0), (245834, 'Love always was and always will be the only real answer. Why else do you think we have been taught so much hate?', 7223, 0), (245835, 'Your love for beauty has been perverted, repressed and savaged by hateful and controlling elements in the world.', 7223, 0), (245836, 'Anyone who hates anyone, only hates themselves.', 7223, 0), (245837, 'Hate when hate acquaints the burns', 42921, 0), (245838, 'I wanted to hate you, but I just couldn''t.', 4894, 0), (245839, 'It''s not hard to confuse love and hate.', 37186, 0), (245840, 'We are all too fixed on wrecking ourselves rather than bettering ourselves.', 4078, 0), (245841, 'It was always like this. When you spoke the truth, they hated you. The more you talked about love, the more they hated you.', 260, 0), (245842, 'Please don''t trouble yourself with my scars. At least not right now, OK?', 23436, 0), (245843, 'They say that people fall in and out of love, but do they, too, fall in hate? Or fall into indifference? It has hindered men for ages the notion that one falls in love rather than decides to truly love, the notion that his lack of control, on the B-side, can also make him fall in hate or indifference without the responsibility to help it or control it.', 230, 0), (245844, 'Children would struggle desperately to feel love for their parents. Rather than hate a parent, in fact, they''d choose to hate themselves. Love and violence became so intertwined for them that when they grew up and got into relationships, only hysteria could set their hearts at ease.', 19310, 0), (245845, 'You need to respect people either good one or bad. Every person in this world have something good and something bad. You need to see the positive side of the person rather than the negative ones. By doing this you can never hate anyone in this world. Some time ago I use to think to shoot few peoples, but seeing the things they gave me when they love me, I use to forget their bad things. They taught me what''s life, how to survive, how to struggle, how to be success, but they also left me on the middle of the desert…… but with due respect and the lessons they gave to me I easily come out from that desert…. And now I am trying to teach all these life experiences to them who need it…….', 15753, 0), (245846, 'she hated everything her parents loved', 6, 0), (245847, 'You are all made of real poop.', 986, 0), (245848, 'I got both hands on her throat and there was nothing inside me but the black madness of that desire to kill her, to close my hands until she turned purple and lay still and there’d be an end to her forever. Let them send me to the chair. Let ’em burn me. All they could do was kill me.', 4498, 0), (245849, 'Knowing a person''s true identity - it feels wonderful & painful at the same time. It feels wonderful because you will know a lot more about him. It feels painful because you only have one choice, it is "acceptance".', 42922, 0), (245850, 'Have you ever noticed how good things go to those who hate?', 25241, 0);
